						<summary>

						<p>[Pāṇḍya], Kōnērinmaikoṇḍān, 10th year = c. 13th Century.</p>						

						<p>Badly damaged. This records a grant of half a <hi rend="italic">vēli</hi> of land by the king as tax-free <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> for offerings to the deity Tiruppaḷḷiyaṟai-Nāchchiyār in the temple. The same son-in-law mentioned in the above record (No. 216) seems to have requested the king for this grant too.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 661.]</p>						

						</summary>
